Key Match Events: Dani Olmo scored the opening goal for Spain in the 51st minute.
Florian Wirtz equalized for Germany in the 89th minute.
Mikel Merino scored the winning goal for Spain in the 119th minute.
Dani Carvajal was sent off after receiving a second yellow card in extra time.
Post-Match Reflections: Dani Olmo emphasized the importance of staying calm and preparing for the semifinals.
Mikel Merino expressed exhaustion and highlighted the team's perseverance and hard work.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at MHPArena in Stuttgart, Germany, with an attendance of 54,000.
Spain will face either Portugal or France in the semifinals.
